The code changes introduce redundant logic and unnecessary complexity in the `update` methods of `DisableForWorkspaceAction` and `DisableGloballyAction`. The main issue is that the state is being recalculated multiple times and then reassigned to the same variable.

**Suggested Refactoring:**

- Remove the redundant recalculation of `state`.
- Simplify the logic by directly setting `this.enabled` based on the conditions.

```typescript
update(): void {
    this.hidden = true;
    if (this.extension && this.extension.local && !this.extension.isWorkspaceScoped && this.workspaceContextService.getWorkbenchState() !== WorkbenchState.EMPTY) {
        const isDefaultChatAgent = ExtensionIdentifier.equals(this.extension.identifier.id, this.productService.defaultChatAgent?.chatExtensionId);
        if (isDefaultChatAgent) return;

        this.hidden = false;
        this.enabled = (
            this.extension.state === ExtensionState.Installed
            && ((this.extension.enablementState === EnablementState.EnabledGlobally && !isDefaultChatAgent)
               || this.extension.enablementState === EnablementState.EnabledWorkspace)
            && this.extensionEnablementService.canChangeWorkspaceEnablement(this.extension.local)
        );
    }
}

override async run(): Promise<any> {
    if (!this.extension) return;

    // ... existing logic ...

    const isDefaultChatAgent = ExtensionIdentifier.equals(this.extension.identifier.id, this.productService.defaultChatAgent?.chatExtensionId);
    if (isDefaultChatAgent) return;

    this.hidden = false;
    this.enabled = (
        this.extension.state === ExtensionState.Installed
        && this.extension.enablementState === EnablementState.EnabledGlobally
        && this.extensionEnablementService.canChangeEnablement(this.extension.local)
    );
}
```

